🌐 What is HTTP?

HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol) is a rule (protocol) used for communication between a web browser (client) and a web server.

🧠 Simple Definition (Interview Style)

👉 HTTP is a protocol used to transfer web pages and data from server to client over the internet.

🌍 Easy Example

When you open a website:

http://example.com

👉 Your browser sends a request
👉 Server sends back a response (web page)

⚙️ How HTTP works
Client (browser) sends request
Server processes it
Server sends response (HTML, images, etc.)

Example:

GET /index.html HTTP/1.1
🔑 Key Features
Works on port 80
Stateless (doesn’t remember previous requests)
Fast but not secure
❌ Problem with HTTP
Data is not encrypted
Hackers can read information (like passwords)
🔐 Solution → HTTPS

👉 Secure version of HTTP (uses encryption)
